biography.content:
I completed my Bachelor’s degree in Nutrition and Food Sciences in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. After graduating with my Bachelor’s degree, I decided that I wanted to further pursue my studies in Canada. I have been in Canada now for six years. I completed my Master’s degree at Mount Saint Vincent University (MSVU) in Applied Human Nutrition in Halifax, Nova Scotia. My career goal is to become a professional nutrition researcher and academic.
I am currently in my second year of my PhD degree in community nutrition, working with Dr. Noreen willows and Dr. Geoff Ball.
